  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Daniel and His Friends Obey God'
      title: Daniel and His Friends Obey God
      number: 1
      content: 'In the third year of the reign of Jehoiakim king of Judah, Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon came to Jerusalem and besieged it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And the Lord gave Jehoiakim king of Judah into his hand, with some
        of the articles of the house of God, which he carried into the land of Shinar
        to the house of his god; and he brought the articles into the treasure house
        of his god.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the king instructed Ashpenaz, the master of his eunuchs, to
        bring some of the children of Israel and some of the king\u2019s descendants
        and some of the nobles, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "young men in whom there  was no blemish, but good-looking, gifted
        in all wisdom, possessing knowledge and quick to understand, who had ability
        to serve in the king\u2019s palace, and whom they might teach the language
        and literature of the Chaldeans. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the king appointed for them a daily provision of the king\u2019s
        delicacies and of the wine which he drank, and three years of training for
        them, so that at the end of that  time they might serve before the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now from among those of the sons of Judah were Daniel, Hananiah,
        Mishael, and Azariah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'To them the chief of the eunuchs gave names: he gave Daniel the 
        name Belteshazzar; to Hananiah, Shadrach; to Mishael, Meshach; and to Azariah,
        Abed-Nego.'
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Daniel purposed in his heart that he would not defile himself
        with the portion of the king\u2019s delicacies, nor with the wine which he
        drank; therefore he requested of the chief of the eunuchs that he might not
        defile himself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now God had brought Daniel into the favor and goodwill of the chief
        of the eunuchs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the chief of the eunuchs said to Daniel, \u201CI fear my lord
        the king, who has appointed your food and drink. For why should he see your
        faces looking worse than the young men who are your age? Then you would endanger
        my head before the king.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Daniel said to the steward whom the chief of the eunuchs had set
        over Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CPlease test your servants for ten days, and let them give us
        vegetables to eat and water to drink. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then let our appearance be examined before you, and the appearance
        of the young men who eat the portion of the king\u2019s delicacies; and as
        you see fit, so deal with your servants.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: So he consented with them in this matter, and tested them ten days.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And at the end of ten days their features appeared better and fatter
        in flesh than all the young men who ate the portion of the king\u2019s delicacies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Thus the steward took away their portion of delicacies and the wine
        that they were to drink, and gave them vegetables.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: As for these four young men, God gave them knowledge and skill in
        all literature and wisdom; and Daniel had understanding in all visions and
        dreams.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now at the end of the days, when the king had said that they should
        be brought in, the chief of the eunuchs brought them in before Nebuchadnezzar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then the king interviewed them, and among them all none was found
        like Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah; therefore they served before
        the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And in all matters of wisdom and understanding about which the king
        examined them, he found them ten times better than all the magicians and
        astrologers who were in all his realm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Thus Daniel continued until the first year of King Cyrus.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Dream"
      title: "Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Dream"
      number: 1
      content: "Now in the second year of Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s reign, Nebuchadnezzar
        had dreams; and his spirit was so troubled that his sleep left him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the king gave the command to call the magicians, the astrologers,
        the sorcerers, and the Chaldeans to tell the king his dreams. So they came
        and stood before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the king said to them, \u201CI have had a dream, and my spirit
        is anxious to know the dream.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the Chaldeans spoke to the king in Aramaic, \u201CO king, live
        forever! Tell your servants the dream, and we will give the interpretation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The king answered and said to the Chaldeans, \u201CMy decision is
        firm: if you do not make known the dream to me, and its interpretation, you
        shall be cut in pieces, and your houses shall be made an ash heap. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "However, if you tell the dream and its interpretation, you shall
        receive from me gifts, rewards, and great honor. Therefore tell me the dream
        and its interpretation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They answered again and said, \u201CLet the king tell his servants
        the dream, and we will give its interpretation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The king answered and said, \u201CI know for certain that you would
        gain time, because you see that my decision is firm: "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "if you do not make known the dream to me, there  is  only one decree
        for you! For you have agreed to speak lying and corrupt words before me till
        the time has changed. Therefore tell me the dream, and I shall know that
        you can give me its interpretation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The Chaldeans answered the king, and said, \u201CThere is not a man
        on earth who can tell the king\u2019s matter; therefore no king, lord, or
        ruler has ever asked such things of any magician, astrologer, or Chaldean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "It  is a difficult thing that the king requests, and there is no
        other who can tell it to the king except the gods, whose dwelling is not
        with flesh.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For this reason the king was angry and very furious, and gave the
        command to destroy all the wise men of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: "13: God Reveals Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Dream"
      title: "God Reveals Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Dream"
      number: 13
      content: So the decree went out, and they began killing the wise men; and they
        sought Daniel and his companions, to kill them.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then with counsel and wisdom Daniel answered Arioch, the captain
        of the king\u2019s guard, who had gone out to kill the wise men of Babylon; "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "he answered and said to Arioch the king\u2019s captain, \u201CWhy
        is the decree from the king so urgent?\u201D Then Arioch made the decision
        known to Daniel."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Daniel went in and asked the king to give him time, that he might
        tell the king the interpretation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Daniel went to his house, and made the decision known to Hananiah,
        Mishael, and Azariah, his companions, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'that they might seek mercies from the God of heaven concerning this
        secret, so that Daniel and his companions might not perish with the rest
        of the wise men of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Then the secret was revealed to Daniel in a night vision. So Daniel
        blessed the God of heaven.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Daniel answered and said:\u201CBlessed be the name of God forever
        and ever,For wisdom and might are His."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And He changes the times and the seasons;He removes kings and raises
        up kings;He gives wisdom to the wiseAnd knowledge to those who have understanding.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: He reveals deep and secret things;He knows what is in the darkness,And
        light dwells with Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Daniel Explains the Dream'
      title: Daniel Explains the Dream
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CI thank You and praise You,O God of my fathers;You have given
        me wisdom and might,And have now made known to me what we asked of You,For
        You have made known to us the king\u2019s demand.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Therefore Daniel went to Arioch, whom the king had appointed to destroy
        the wise men of Babylon. He went and said thus to him: \u201CDo not destroy
        the wise men of Babylon; take me before the king, and I will tell the king
        the interpretation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Arioch quickly brought Daniel before the king, and said thus
        to him, \u201CI have found a man of the captives of Judah, who will make
        known to the king the interpretation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "The king answered and said to Daniel, whose name was Belteshazzar,
        \u201CAre you able to make known to me the dream which I have seen, and its
        interpretation?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Daniel answered in the presence of the king, and said, \u201CThe
        secret which the king has demanded, the wise men, the astrologers, the magicians,
        and the soothsayers cannot declare to the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But there is a God in heaven who reveals secrets, and He has made
        known to King Nebuchadnezzar what will be in the latter days. Your dream,
        and the visions of your head upon your bed, were these: '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'As for you, O king, thoughts came to your mind  while on your bed,
        about what would come to pass after this; and He who reveals secrets has
        made known to you what will be. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: But as for me, this secret has not been revealed to me because I have
        more wisdom than anyone living, but for our sakes who make known the interpretation
        to the king, and that you may know the thoughts of your heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CYou, O king, were watching; and behold, a great image! This
        great image, whose splendor was excellent, stood before you; and its form
        was awesome. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "This image\u2019s head was of fine gold, its chest and arms of silver,
        its belly and thighs of bronze, "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'its legs of iron, its feet partly of iron and partly of clay. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'You watched while a stone was cut out without hands, which struck
        the image on its feet of iron and clay, and broke them in pieces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: Then the iron, the clay, the bronze, the silver, and the gold were
        crushed together, and became like chaff from the summer threshing floors;
        the wind carried them away so that no trace of them was found. And the stone
        that struck the image became a great mountain and filled the whole earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CThis is the dream. Now we will tell the interpretation of it
        before the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'You, O king, are a king of kings. For the God of heaven has given
        you a kingdom, power, strength, and glory; '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "and wherever the children of men dwell, or the beasts of the field
        and the birds of the heaven, He has given them into your hand, and has made
        you ruler over them all\u2014you are this head of gold. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'But after you shall arise another kingdom inferior to yours; then
        another, a third kingdom of bronze, which shall rule over all the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And the fourth kingdom shall be as strong as iron, inasmuch as iron
        breaks in pieces and shatters everything; and like iron that crushes, that 
        kingdom will break in pieces and crush all the others. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Whereas you saw the feet and toes, partly of potter\u2019s clay and
        partly of iron, the kingdom shall be divided; yet the strength of the iron
        shall be in it, just as you saw the iron mixed with ceramic clay. "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And as the toes of the feet were partly of iron and partly of clay,
        so the kingdom shall be partly strong and partly fragile. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'As you saw iron mixed with ceramic clay, they will mingle with the
        seed of men; but they will not adhere to one another, just as iron does not
        mix with clay. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And in the days of these kings the God of heaven will set up a kingdom
        which shall never be destroyed; and the kingdom shall not be left to other
        people; it shall break in pieces and consume all these kingdoms, and it shall
        stand forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: Daniel and His Friends Promoted'
      title: Daniel and His Friends Promoted
      number: 45
      content: "Inasmuch as you saw that the stone was cut out of the mountain without
        hands, and that it broke in pieces the iron, the bronze, the clay, the silver,
        and the gold\u2014the great God has made known to the king what will come
        to pass after this. The dream is certain, and its interpretation is sure.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Then King Nebuchadnezzar fell on his face, prostrate before Daniel,
        and commanded that they should present an offering and incense to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "The king answered Daniel, and said, \u201CTruly your God is the God
        of gods, the Lord of kings, and a revealer of secrets, since you could reveal
        this secret.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Then the king promoted Daniel and gave him many great gifts; and
        he made him ruler over the whole province of Babylon, and chief administrator
        over all the wise men of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: Also Daniel petitioned the king, and he set Shadrach, Meshach, and
        Abed-Nego over the affairs of the province of Babylon; but Daniel sat in
        the gate of the king.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Image of Gold'
      title: The Image of Gold
      number: 1
      content: 'Nebuchadnezzar the king made an image of gold, whose height was sixty
        cubits and its width six cubits. He set it up in the plain of Dura, in the
        province of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And King Nebuchadnezzar sent word to gather together the satraps,
        the administrators, the governors, the counselors, the treasurers, the judges,
        the magistrates, and all the officials of the provinces, to come to the dedication
        of the image which King Nebuchadnezzar had set up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So the satraps, the administrators, the governors, the counselors,
        the treasurers, the judges, the magistrates, and all the officials of the
        provinces gathered together for the dedication of the image that King Nebuchadnezzar
        had set up; and they stood before the image that Nebuchadnezzar had set up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then a herald cried aloud: \u201CTo you it is commanded, O peoples,
        nations, and languages, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'that at the time you hear the sound of the horn, flute, harp, lyre,
        and psaltery, in symphony with all kinds of music, you shall fall down and
        worship the gold image that King Nebuchadnezzar has set up; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and whoever does not fall down and worship shall be cast immediately
        into the midst of a burning fiery furnace.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Daniel\u2019s Friends Disobey the King"
      title: "Daniel\u2019s Friends Disobey the King"
      number: 7
      content: So at that time, when all the people heard the sound of the horn,
        flute, harp, and lyre, in symphony with all kinds of music, all the people,
        nations, and languages fell down and worshiped the gold image which King
        Nebuchadnezzar had set up.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Therefore at that time certain Chaldeans came forward and accused
        the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "They spoke and said to King Nebuchadnezzar, \u201CO king, live forever! "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You, O king, have made a decree that everyone who hears the sound
        of the horn, flute, harp, lyre, and psaltery, in symphony with all kinds
        of music, shall fall down and worship the gold image; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and whoever does not fall down and worship shall be cast into the
        midst of a burning fiery furnace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "There are certain Jews whom you have set over the affairs of the
        province of Babylon: Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-Nego; these men, O king,
        have not paid due regard to you. They do not serve your gods or worship the
        gold image which you have set up.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Nebuchadnezzar, in rage and fury, gave the command to bring
        Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-Nego. So they brought these men before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Nebuchadnezzar spoke, saying to them, \u201CIs  it true, Shadrach,
        Meshach, and Abed-Nego, that you do not serve my gods or worship the gold
        image which I have set up? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now if you are ready at the time you hear the sound of the horn,
        flute, harp, lyre, and psaltery, in symphony with all kinds of music, and
        you fall down and worship the image which I have made, good! But if you do
        not worship, you shall be cast immediately into the midst of a burning fiery
        furnace. And who is the god who will deliver you from my hands?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-Nego answered and said to the king, \u201CO
        Nebuchadnezzar, we have no need to answer you in this matter. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'If that is  the  case, our God whom we serve is able to deliver us
        from the burning fiery furnace, and He will deliver us from your hand, O
        king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Saved in Fiery Trial'
      title: Saved in Fiery Trial
      number: 18
      content: "But if not, let it be known to you, O king, that we do not serve
        your gods, nor will we worship the gold image which you have set up.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then Nebuchadnezzar was full of fury, and the expression on his face
        changed toward Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-Nego. He spoke and commanded that
        they heat the furnace seven times more than it was usually heated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And he commanded certain mighty men of valor who were in his army
        to bind Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-Nego, and cast them into the burning
        fiery furnace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then these men were bound in their coats, their trousers, their turbans,
        and their other garments, and were cast into the midst of the burning fiery
        furnace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Therefore, because the king\u2019s command was urgent, and the furnace
        exceedingly hot, the flame of the fire killed those men who took up Shadrach,
        Meshach, and Abed-Nego. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And these three men, Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-Nego, fell down bound
        into the midst of the burning fiery furnace.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then King Nebuchadnezzar was astonished; and he rose in haste and
        spoke, saying to his counselors, \u201CDid we not cast three men bound into
        the midst of the fire?\u201DThey answered and said to the king, \u201CTrue,
        O king.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Nebuchadnezzar Praises God'
      title: Nebuchadnezzar Praises God
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CLook!\u201D he answered, \u201CI see four men loose, walking
        in the midst of the fire; and they are not hurt, and the form of the fourth
        is like the Son of God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Nebuchadnezzar went near the mouth of the burning fiery furnace
        and spoke, saying, \u201CShadrach, Meshach, and Abed-Nego, servants of the
        Most High God, come out, and come here.\u201D Then Shadrach, Meshach, and
        Abed-Nego came from the midst of the fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And the satraps, administrators, governors, and the king\u2019s counselors
        gathered together, and they saw these men on whose bodies the fire had no
        power; the hair of their head was not singed nor were their garments affected,
        and the smell of fire was not on them."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Nebuchadnezzar spoke, saying, \u201CBlessed be the God of Shadrach,
        Meshach, and Abed-Nego, who sent His Angel and delivered His servants who
        trusted in Him, and they have frustrated the king\u2019s word, and yielded
        their bodies, that they should not serve nor worship any god except their
        own God! "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Therefore I make a decree that any people, nation, or language which
        speaks anything amiss against the God of Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-Nego
        shall be cut in pieces, and their houses shall be made an ash heap; because
        there is no other God who can deliver like this.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Then the king promoted Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-Nego in the province
        of Babylon.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Second Dream"
      title: "Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Second Dream"
      number: 1
      content: Nebuchadnezzar the king,To all peoples, nations, and languages that
        dwell in all the earth:Peace be multiplied to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: I thought it good to declare the signs and wonders that the Most High
        God has worked for me.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: How great are His signs,And how mighty His wonders!His kingdom is 
        an everlasting kingdom,And His dominion is from generation to generation.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I, Nebuchadnezzar, was at rest in my house, and flourishing in my
        palace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I saw a dream which made me afraid, and the thoughts on my bed and
        the visions of my head troubled me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore I issued a decree to bring in all the wise men of Babylon
        before me, that they might make known to me the interpretation of the dream. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the magicians, the astrologers, the Chaldeans, and the soothsayers
        came in, and I told them the dream; but they did not make known to me its
        interpretation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But at last Daniel came before me (his name is Belteshazzar, according
        to the name of my god; in him is the Spirit of the Holy God), and I told
        the dream before him, saying:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CBelteshazzar, chief of the magicians, because I know that the
        Spirit of the Holy God is in you, and no secret troubles you, explain to
        me the visions of my dream that I have seen, and its interpretation."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThese were the visions of my head while on my bed:I was looking,
        and behold,A tree in the midst of the earth,And its height was great."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The tree grew and became strong;Its height reached to the heavens,And
        it could be seen to the ends of all the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Its leaves were lovely,Its fruit abundant,And in it was food for all.The
        beasts of the field found shade under it,The birds of the heavens dwelt in
        its branches,And all flesh was fed from it.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CI saw in the visions of my head while on my bed, and there
        was a watcher, a holy one, coming down from heaven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He cried aloud and said thus:\u2018Chop down the tree and cut off
        its branches,Strip off its leaves and scatter its fruit.Let the beasts get
        out from under it,And the birds from its branches."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Nevertheless leave the stump and roots in the earth,Bound with a band
        of iron and bronze,In the tender grass of the field.Let it be wet with the
        dew of heaven,And let him graze with the beastsOn the grass of the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Let his heart be changed from that  of a man,Let him be given the
        heart of a beast,And let seven times pass over him.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018This decision is by the decree of the watchers,And the sentence
        by the word of the holy ones,In order that the living may knowThat the Most
        High rules in the kingdom of men,Gives it to whomever He will,And sets over
        it the lowest of men.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Daniel Explains the Second Dream'
      title: Daniel Explains the Second Dream
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThis dream I, King Nebuchadnezzar, have seen. Now you, Belteshazzar,
        declare its interpretation, since all the wise men of my kingdom are not
        able to make known to me the interpretation; but you are able, for the Spirit
        of the Holy God is in you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Daniel, whose name was Belteshazzar, was astonished for a time,
        and his thoughts troubled him. So the king spoke, and said, \u201CBelteshazzar,
        do not let the dream or its interpretation trouble you.\u201D Belteshazzar
        answered and said, \u201CMy lord, may  the dream concern those who hate you,
        and its interpretation concern your enemies!"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThe tree that you saw, which grew and became strong, whose
        height reached to the heavens and which could  be seen by all the earth, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "whose leaves were lovely and its fruit abundant, in which was food
        for all, under which the beasts of the field dwelt, and in whose branches
        the birds of the heaven had their home\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: it is you, O king, who have grown and become strong; for your greatness
        has grown and reaches to the heavens, and your dominion to the end of the
        earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CAnd inasmuch as the king saw a watcher, a holy one, coming
        down from heaven and saying, \u2018Chop down the tree and destroy it, but
        leave its stump and roots in the earth, bound with a band of iron and bronze
        in the tender grass of the field; let it be wet with the dew of heaven, and
        let him graze with the beasts of the field, till seven times pass over him\u2019; "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'this is the interpretation, O king, and this is the decree of the
        Most High, which has come upon my lord the king: '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: They shall drive you from men, your dwelling shall be with the beasts
        of the field, and they shall make you eat grass like oxen. They shall wet
        you with the dew of heaven, and seven times shall pass over you, till you
        know that the Most High rules in the kingdom of men, and gives it to whomever
        He chooses.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CAnd inasmuch as they gave the command to leave the stump and
        roots of the tree, your kingdom shall be assured to you, after you come to
        know that Heaven rules. "
      comments: []
    - name: "27: Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Humiliation"
      title: "Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Humiliation"
      number: 27
      content: "Therefore, O king, let my advice be acceptable to you; break off
        your sins by being righteous, and your iniquities by showing mercy to the
        poor. Perhaps there may be a lengthening of your prosperity.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'All this came upon King Nebuchadnezzar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'At the end of the twelve months he was walking about the royal palace
        of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "The king spoke, saying, \u201CIs not this great Babylon, that I have
        built for a royal dwelling by my mighty power and for the honor of my majesty?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "While the word was  still in the king\u2019s mouth, a voice fell
        from heaven: \u201CKing Nebuchadnezzar, to you it is spoken: the kingdom
        has departed from you! "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And they shall drive you from men, and your dwelling shall  be with
        the beasts of the field. They shall make you eat grass like oxen; and seven
        times shall pass over you, until you know that the Most High rules in the
        kingdom of men, and gives it to whomever He chooses.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: Nebuchadnezzar Praises God'
      title: Nebuchadnezzar Praises God
      number: 33
      content: "That very hour the word was fulfilled concerning Nebuchadnezzar;
        he was driven from men and ate grass like oxen; his body was wet with the
        dew of heaven till his hair had grown like eagles\u2019 feathers and his
        nails like birds\u2019 claws."
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: And at the end of the time I, Nebuchadnezzar, lifted my eyes to heaven,
        and my understanding returned to me; and I blessed the Most High and praised
        and honored Him who lives forever:For His dominion is  an everlasting dominion,And
        His kingdom is from generation to generation.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "All the inhabitants of the earth are reputed as nothing;He does according
        to His will in the army of heavenAnd among the inhabitants of the earth.No
        one can restrain His handOr say to Him, \u201CWhat have You done?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'At the same time my reason returned to me, and for the glory of my
        kingdom, my honor and splendor returned to me. My counselors and nobles resorted
        to me, I was restored to my kingdom, and excellent majesty was added to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: Now I, Nebuchadnezzar, praise and extol and honor the King of heaven,
        all of whose works are truth, and His ways justice. And those who walk in
        pride He is able to put down.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Belshazzar\u2019s Feast"
      title: "Belshazzar\u2019s Feast"
      number: 1
      content: 'Belshazzar the king made a great feast for a thousand of his lords,
        and drank wine in the presence of the thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'While he tasted the wine, Belshazzar gave the command to bring the
        gold and silver vessels which his father Nebuchadnezzar had taken from the
        temple which had  been in Jerusalem, that the king and his lords, his wives,
        and his concubines might drink from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then they brought the gold vessels that had been taken from the temple
        of the house of God which had  been in Jerusalem; and the king and his lords,
        his wives, and his concubines drank from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: They drank wine, and praised the gods of gold and silver, bronze and
        iron, wood and stone.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "In the same hour the fingers of a man\u2019s hand appeared and wrote
        opposite the lampstand on the plaster of the wall of the king\u2019s palace;
        and the king saw the part of the hand that wrote. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the king\u2019s countenance changed, and his thoughts troubled
        him, so that the joints of his hips were loosened and his knees knocked against
        each other. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The king cried aloud to bring in the astrologers, the Chaldeans,
        and the soothsayers. The king spoke, saying to the wise men of Babylon, \u201CWhoever
        reads this writing, and tells me its interpretation, shall be clothed with
        purple and have a chain of gold around his neck; and he shall be the third
        ruler in the kingdom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now all the king\u2019s wise men came, but they could not read the
        writing, or make known to the king its interpretation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Then King Belshazzar was greatly troubled, his countenance was changed,
        and his lords were astonished.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The queen, because of the words of the king and his lords, came to
        the banquet hall. The queen spoke, saying, \u201CO king, live forever! Do
        not let your thoughts trouble you, nor let your countenance change. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "There is a man in your kingdom in whom is the Spirit of the Holy
        God. And in the days of your father, light and understanding and wisdom,
        like the wisdom of the gods, were found in him; and King Nebuchadnezzar your
        father\u2014your father the king\u2014made him chief of the magicians, astrologers,
        Chaldeans, and soothsayers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Writing on the Wall Explained'
      title: The Writing on the Wall Explained
      number: 12
      content: "Inasmuch as an excellent spirit, knowledge, understanding, interpreting
        dreams, solving riddles, and explaining enigmas were found in this Daniel,
        whom the king named Belteshazzar, now let Daniel be called, and he will give
        the interpretation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Daniel was brought in before the king. The king spoke, and said
        to Daniel, \u201CAre you that Daniel who is one of the captives from Judah,
        whom my father the king brought from Judah? "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I have heard of you, that the Spirit of God is in you, and that light
        and understanding and excellent wisdom are found in you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now the wise men, the astrologers, have been brought in before me,
        that they should read this writing and make known to me its interpretation,
        but they could not give the interpretation of the thing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And I have heard of you, that you can give interpretations and explain
        enigmas. Now if you can read the writing and make known to me its interpretation,
        you shall be clothed with purple and have a chain of gold around your neck,
        and shall be the third ruler in the kingdom.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Daniel answered, and said before the king, \u201CLet your gifts
        be for yourself, and give your rewards to another; yet I will read the writing
        to the king, and make known to him the interpretation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'O king, the Most High God gave Nebuchadnezzar your father a kingdom
        and majesty, glory and honor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And because of the majesty that He gave him, all peoples, nations,
        and languages trembled and feared before him. Whomever he wished, he executed;
        whomever he wished, he kept alive; whomever he wished, he set up; and whomever
        he wished, he put down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But when his heart was lifted up, and his spirit was hardened in
        pride, he was deposed from his kingly throne, and they took his glory from
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Then he was driven from the sons of men, his heart was made like the
        beasts, and his dwelling was with the wild donkeys. They fed him with grass
        like oxen, and his body was wet with the dew of heaven, till he knew that
        the Most High God rules in the kingdom of men, and appoints over it whomever
        He chooses.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CBut you his son, Belshazzar, have not humbled your heart, although
        you knew all this. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And you have lifted yourself up against the Lord of heaven. They
        have brought the vessels of His house before you, and you and your lords,
        your wives and your concubines, have drunk wine from them. And you have praised
        the gods of silver and gold, bronze and iron, wood and stone, which do not
        see or hear or know; and the God who holds your breath in His hand and owns
        all your ways, you have not glorified. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Then the fingers of the hand were sent from Him, and this writing
        was written.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CAnd this is the inscription that was written:MENE, MENE, TEKEL,
        UPHARSIN."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'This is the interpretation of each word. MENE: God has numbered your
        kingdom, and finished it; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'TEKEL: You have been weighed in the balances, and found wanting; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "PERES: Your kingdom has been divided, and given to the Medes and
        Persians.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "29: Belshazzar\u2019s Fall"
      title: "Belshazzar\u2019s Fall"
      number: 29
      content: Then Belshazzar gave the command, and they clothed Daniel with purple
        and put a chain of gold around his neck, and made a proclamation concerning
        him that he should be the third ruler in the kingdom.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'That very night Belshazzar, king of the Chaldeans, was slain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: And Darius the Mede received the kingdom, being about sixty-two years
        old.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Plot Against Daniel'
      title: The Plot Against Daniel
      number: 1
      content: 'It pleased Darius to set over the kingdom one hundred and twenty
        satraps, to be over the whole kingdom; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and over these, three governors, of whom Daniel was one, that the
        satraps might give account to them, so that the king would suffer no loss. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then this Daniel distinguished himself above the governors and satraps,
        because an excellent spirit was in him; and the king gave thought to setting
        him over the whole realm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So the governors and satraps sought to find some charge against Daniel
        concerning the kingdom; but they could find no charge or fault, because he
        was faithful; nor was there any error or fault found in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then these men said, \u201CWe shall not find any charge against this
        Daniel unless we find it against him concerning the law of his God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So these governors and satraps thronged before the king, and said
        thus to him: \u201CKing Darius, live forever! "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All the governors of the kingdom, the administrators and satraps,
        the counselors and advisors, have consulted together to establish a royal
        statute and to make a firm decree, that whoever petitions any god or man
        for thirty days, except you, O king, shall be cast into the den of lions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now, O king, establish the decree and sign the writing, so that it
        cannot be changed, according to the law of the Medes and Persians, which
        does not alter.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Daniel in the Lions\u2019 Den"
      title: "Daniel in the Lions\u2019 Den"
      number: 9
      content: Therefore King Darius signed the written decree.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Now when Daniel knew that the writing was signed, he went home. And
        in his upper room, with his windows open toward Jerusalem, he knelt down
        on his knees three times that day, and prayed and gave thanks before his
        God, as was his custom since early days.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then these men assembled and found Daniel praying and making supplication
        before his God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And they went before the king, and spoke concerning the king\u2019s
        decree: \u201CHave you not signed a decree that every man who petitions any
        god or man within thirty days, except you, O king, shall be cast into the
        den of lions?\u201DThe king answered and said, \u201CThe thing is true, according
        to the law of the Medes and Persians, which does not alter.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So they answered and said before the king, \u201CThat Daniel, who
        is one of the captives from Judah, does not show due regard for you, O king,
        or for the decree that you have signed, but makes his petition three times
        a day.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the king, when he heard these words, was greatly displeased with
        himself, and set his heart on Daniel to deliver him; and he labored till
        the going down of the sun to deliver him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then these men approached the king, and said to the king, \u201CKnow,
        O king, that it  is  the law of the Medes and Persians that no decree or
        statute which the king establishes may be changed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So the king gave the command, and they brought Daniel and cast him
        into the den of lions. But the king spoke, saying to Daniel, \u201CYour God,
        whom you serve continually, He will deliver you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Daniel Saved from the Lions'
      title: Daniel Saved from the Lions
      number: 17
      content: Then a stone was brought and laid on the mouth of the den, and the
        king sealed it with his own signet ring and with the signets of his lords,
        that the purpose concerning Daniel might not be changed.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the king went to his palace and spent the night fasting; and
        no musicians were brought before him. Also his sleep went from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then the king arose very early in the morning and went in haste to
        the den of lions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And when he came to the den, he cried out with a lamenting voice
        to Daniel. The king spoke, saying to Daniel, \u201CDaniel, servant of the
        living God, has your God, whom you serve continually, been able to deliver
        you from the lions?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Daniel said to the king, \u201CO king, live forever! "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "My God sent His angel and shut the lions\u2019 mouths, so that they
        have not hurt me, because I was found innocent before Him; and also, O king,
        I have done no wrong before you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Darius Honors God'
      title: Darius Honors God
      number: 23
      content: Now the king was exceedingly glad for him, and commanded that they
        should take Daniel up out of the den. So Daniel was taken up out of the den,
        and no injury whatever was found on him, because he believed in his God.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the king gave the command, and they brought those men who had
        accused Daniel, and they cast them into the den of lions\u2014them, their
        children, and their wives; and the lions overpowered them, and broke all
        their bones in pieces before they ever came to the bottom of the den."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Then King Darius wrote:To all peoples, nations, and languages that
        dwell in all the earth:Peace be multiplied to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: I make a decree that in every dominion of my kingdom men  must  tremble
        and fear before the God of Daniel.For He is the living God,And steadfast
        forever;His kingdom is  the  one which shall not be destroyed,And His dominion
        shall  endure to the end.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: He delivers and rescues,And He works signs and wondersIn heaven and
        on earth,Who has delivered Daniel from the power of the lions.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: So this Daniel prospered in the reign of Darius and in the reign of
        Cyrus the Persian.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Vision of the Four Beasts'
      title: Vision of the Four Beasts
      number: 1
      content: In the first year of Belshazzar king of Babylon, Daniel had a dream
        and visions of his head while on his bed. Then he wrote down the dream, telling
        the main facts.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Daniel spoke, saying, \u201CI saw in my vision by night, and behold,
        the four winds of heaven were stirring up the Great Sea. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And four great beasts came up from the sea, each different from the
        other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The first was  like a lion, and had eagle\u2019s wings. I watched
        till its wings were plucked off; and it was lifted up from the earth and
        made to stand on two feet like a man, and a man\u2019s heart was given to
        it."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CAnd suddenly another beast, a second, like a bear. It was raised
        up on one side, and had three ribs in its mouth between its teeth. And they
        said thus to it: \u2018Arise, devour much flesh!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAfter this I looked, and there was another, like a leopard,
        which had on its back four wings of a bird. The beast also had four heads,
        and dominion was given to it."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAfter this I saw in the night visions, and behold, a fourth
        beast, dreadful and terrible, exceedingly strong. It had huge iron teeth;
        it was devouring, breaking in pieces, and trampling the residue with its
        feet. It was different from all the beasts that were before it, and it had
        ten horns. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Vision of the Ancient of Days'
      title: Vision of the Ancient of Days
      number: 8
      content: I was considering the horns, and there was another horn, a little
        one, coming up among them, before whom three of the first horns were plucked
        out by the roots. And there, in this horn, were eyes like the eyes of a man,
        and a mouth speaking pompous words.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CI watched till thrones were put in place,And the Ancient of
        Days was seated;His garment was white as snow,And the hair of His head was
        like pure wool.His throne was a fiery flame,Its wheels a burning fire;"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: A fiery stream issuedAnd came forth from before Him.A thousand thousands
        ministered to Him;Ten thousand times ten thousand stood before Him.The court
        was seated,And the books were opened.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI watched then because of the sound of the pompous words which
        the horn was speaking; I watched till the beast was slain, and its body destroyed
        and given to the burning flame. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: As for the rest of the beasts, they had their dominion taken away,
        yet their lives were prolonged for a season and a time.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CI was watching in the night visions,And behold, One like the
        Son of Man,Coming with the clouds of heaven!He came to the Ancient of Days,And
        they brought Him near before Him."
      comments: []
    - name: "14: Daniel\u2019s Visions Interpreted"
      title: "Daniel\u2019s Visions Interpreted"
      number: 14
      content: Then to Him was given dominion and glory and a kingdom,That all peoples,
        nations, and languages should serve Him.His dominion is  an everlasting dominion,Which
        shall not pass away,And His kingdom the  oneWhich shall not be destroyed.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CI, Daniel, was grieved in my spirit within my body, and the
        visions of my head troubled me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I came near to one of those who stood by, and asked him the truth
        of all this. So he told me and made known to me the interpretation of these
        things: '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Those great beasts, which are four, are four kings which arise
        out of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But the saints of the Most High shall receive the kingdom, and possess
        the kingdom forever, even forever and ever.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThen I wished to know the truth about the fourth beast, which
        was different from all the others, exceedingly dreadful, with its teeth of
        iron and its nails of bronze, which devoured, broke in pieces, and trampled
        the residue with its feet; "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: and the ten horns that were on its head, and the other horn which
        came up, before which three fell, namely, that horn which had eyes and a
        mouth which spoke pompous words, whose appearance was greater than his fellows.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CI was watching; and the same horn was making war against the
        saints, and prevailing against them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: until the Ancient of Days came, and a judgment was made in  favor
        of the saints of the Most High, and the time came for the saints to possess
        the kingdom.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CThus he said:\u2018The fourth beast shall beA fourth kingdom
        on earth,Which shall be different from all other kingdoms,And shall devour
        the whole earth,Trample it and break it in pieces."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: The ten horns are ten kingsWho shall arise from this kingdom.And another
        shall rise after them;He shall be different from the first ones,And shall
        subdue three kings.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: He shall speak pompous words against the Most High,Shall persecute
        the saints of the Most High,And shall intend to change times and law.Then
        the  saints shall be given into his handFor a time and times and half a time.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u2018But the court shall be seated,And they shall take away his
        dominion,To consume and destroy it forever."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then the kingdom and dominion,And the greatness of the kingdoms under
        the whole heaven,Shall be given to the people, the saints of the Most High.His
        kingdom is an everlasting kingdom,And all dominions shall serve and obey
        Him.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CThis is the end of the account. As for me, Daniel, my thoughts
        greatly troubled me, and my countenance changed; but I kept the matter in
        my heart.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Vision of a Ram and a Goat'
      title: Vision of a Ram and a Goat
      number: 1
      content: "In the third year of the reign of King Belshazzar a vision appeared
        to me\u2014to me, Daniel\u2014after the one that appeared to me the first
        time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I saw in the vision, and it so happened while I was looking, that
        I was in Shushan, the citadel, which is in the province of Elam; and I saw
        in the vision that I was by the River Ulai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then I lifted my eyes and saw, and there, standing beside the river,
        was a ram which had two horns, and the two horns were high; but one was 
        higher than the other, and the higher one came up last. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: I saw the ram pushing westward, northward, and southward, so that
        no animal could withstand him; nor was  there  any that could deliver from
        his hand, but he did according to his will and became great.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And as I was considering, suddenly a male goat came from the west,
        across the surface of the whole earth, without touching the ground; and the
        goat had a notable horn between his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then he came to the ram that had two horns, which I had seen standing
        beside the river, and ran at him with furious power. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: And I saw him confronting the ram; he was moved with rage against
        him, attacked the ram, and broke his two horns. There was no power in the
        ram to withstand him, but he cast him down to the ground and trampled him;
        and there was no one that could deliver the ram from his hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Therefore the male goat grew very great; but when he became strong,
        the large horn was broken, and in place of it four notable ones came up toward
        the four winds of heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And out of one of them came a little horn which grew exceedingly
        great toward the south, toward the east, and toward the Glorious Land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And it grew up to the host of heaven; and it cast down some of the
        host and some of the stars to the ground, and trampled them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He even exalted himself as high as the Prince of the host; and by
        him the daily sacrifices were taken away, and the place of His sanctuary
        was cast down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Because of transgression, an army was given over to  the  horn to
        oppose the daily sacrifices; and he cast truth down to the ground. He did
        all  this and prospered.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then I heard a holy one speaking; and another holy one said to that
        certain one who was speaking, \u201CHow long will the vision be, concerning
        the daily sacrifices and the transgression of desolation, the giving of both
        the sanctuary and the host to be trampled underfoot?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Gabriel Interprets the Vision'
      title: Gabriel Interprets the Vision
      number: 14
      content: "And he said to me, \u201CFor two thousand three hundred days; then
        the sanctuary shall be cleansed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then it happened, when I, Daniel, had seen the vision and was seeking
        the meaning, that suddenly there stood before me one having the appearance
        of a man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And I heard a man\u2019s voice between the  banks  of the Ulai, who
        called, and said, \u201CGabriel, make this man understand the vision.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So he came near where I stood, and when he came I was afraid and
        fell on my face; but he said to me, \u201CUnderstand, son of man, that the
        vision refers to the time of the end.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now, as he was speaking with me, I was in a deep sleep with my face
        to the ground; but he touched me, and stood me upright. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he said, \u201CLook, I am making known to you what shall happen
        in the latter time of the indignation; for at the appointed time the end
        shall  be.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The ram which you saw, having the two horns\u2014they  are the kings
        of Media and Persia. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the male goat is the kingdom of Greece. The large horn that is
        between its eyes is the first king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: As for the broken horn and the four that stood up in its place, four
        kingdoms shall arise out of that nation, but not with its power.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CAnd in the latter time of their kingdom,When the transgressors
        have reached their fullness,A king shall arise,Having fierce features,Who
        understands sinister schemes."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: His power shall be mighty, but not by his own power;He shall destroy
        fearfully,And shall prosper and thrive;He shall destroy the mighty, and also
        the holy people.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CThrough his cunningHe shall cause deceit to prosper under his
        rule;And he shall exalt himself in his heart.He shall destroy many in their
        prosperity.He shall even rise against the Prince of princes;But he shall
        be broken without human means."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CAnd the vision of the evenings and morningsWhich was told is
        true;Therefore seal up the vision,For it  refers to many days in  the  future.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And I, Daniel, fainted and was sick for days; afterward I arose and
        went about the king\u2019s business. I was astonished by the vision, but
        no one understood it."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Daniel\u2019s Prayer for the People"
      title: "Daniel\u2019s Prayer for the People"
      number: 1
      content: "In the first year of Darius the son of Ahasuerus, of the lineage
        of the Medes, who was made king over the realm of the Chaldeans\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: in the first year of his reign I, Daniel, understood by the books
        the number of the years specified by the word of the Lord through Jeremiah
        the prophet, that He would accomplish seventy years in the desolations of
        Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then I set my face toward the Lord God to make request by prayer
        and supplications, with fasting, sackcloth, and ashes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And I prayed to the Lord my God, and made confession, and said, \u201CO
        Lord, great and awesome God, who keeps His covenant and mercy with those
        who love Him, and with those who keep His commandments, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'we have sinned and committed iniquity, we have done wickedly and
        rebelled, even by departing from Your precepts and Your judgments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Neither have we heeded Your servants the prophets, who spoke in Your
        name to our kings and our princes, to our fathers and all the people of the
        land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "O Lord, righteousness belongs to You, but to us shame of face, as
        it  is this day\u2014to the men of Judah, to the inhabitants of Jerusalem
        and all Israel, those near and those far off in all the countries to which
        You have driven them, because of the unfaithfulness which they have committed
        against You."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CO Lord, to us belongs shame of face, to our kings, our princes,
        and our fathers, because we have sinned against You. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'To the Lord our God belong mercy and forgiveness, though we have
        rebelled against Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'We have not obeyed the voice of the Lord our God, to walk in His
        laws, which He set before us by His servants the prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Yes, all Israel has transgressed Your law, and has departed so as
        not to obey Your voice; therefore the curse and the oath written in the Law
        of Moses the servant of God have been poured out on us, because we have sinned
        against Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And He has confirmed His words, which He spoke against us and against
        our judges who judged us, by bringing upon us a great disaster; for under
        the whole heaven such has never been done as what has been done to Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CAs it  is written in the Law of Moses, all this disaster has
        come upon us; yet we have not made our prayer before the Lord our God, that
        we might turn from our iniquities and understand Your truth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore the Lord has kept the disaster in mind, and brought it
        upon us; for the Lord our God is righteous in all the works which He does,
        though we have not obeyed His voice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And now, O Lord our God, who brought Your people out of the land
        of Egypt with a mighty hand, and made Yourself a name, as it  is this day\u2014we
        have sinned, we have done wickedly!"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CO Lord, according to all Your righteousness, I pray, let Your
        anger and Your fury be turned away from Your city Jerusalem, Your holy mountain;
        because for our sins, and for the iniquities of our fathers, Jerusalem and
        Your people are a reproach to all those around us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now therefore, our God, hear the prayer of Your servant, and his
        supplications, and for the Lord\u2019s sake cause Your face to shine on Your
        sanctuary, which is desolate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'O my God, incline Your ear and hear; open Your eyes and see our desolations,
        and the city which is called by Your name; for we do not present our supplications
        before You because of our righteous deeds, but because of Your great mercies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Seventy-Weeks Prophecy'
      title: The Seventy-Weeks Prophecy
      number: 19
      content: "O Lord, hear! O Lord, forgive! O Lord, listen and act! Do not delay
        for Your own sake, my God, for Your city and Your people are called by Your
        name.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now while I was speaking, praying, and confessing my sin and the
        sin of my people Israel, and presenting my supplication before the Lord my
        God for the holy mountain of my God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'yes, while I was speaking in prayer, the man Gabriel, whom I had
        seen in the vision at the beginning, being caused to fly swiftly, reached
        me about the time of the evening offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And he informed me, and talked with me, and said, \u201CO Daniel,
        I have now come forth to give you skill to understand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'At the beginning of your supplications the command went out, and
        I have come to tell you, for you are greatly beloved; therefore consider
        the matter, and understand the vision:'
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CSeventy weeks are determinedFor your people and for your holy
        city,To finish the transgression,To make an end of sins,To make reconciliation
        for iniquity,To bring in everlasting righteousness,To seal up vision and
        prophecy,And to anoint the Most Holy."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CKnow therefore and understand,That from the going forth of
        the commandTo restore and build JerusalemUntil Messiah the Prince,There 
        shall  be seven weeks and sixty-two weeks;The street shall be built again,
        and the wall,Even in troublesome times."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CAnd after the sixty-two weeksMessiah shall be cut off, but
        not for Himself;And the people of the prince who is to comeShall destroy
        the city and the sanctuary.The end of it shall  be with a flood,And till
        the end of the war desolations are determined."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then he shall confirm a covenant with many for one week;But in the
        middle of the weekHe shall bring an end to sacrifice and offering.And on
        the wing of abominations shall be one who makes desolate,Even until the consummation,
        which is determined,Is poured out on the desolate.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Vision of the Glorious Man'
      title: Vision of the Glorious Man
      number: 1
      content: 'In the third year of Cyrus king of Persia a message was revealed
        to Daniel, whose name was called Belteshazzar. The message was true, but
        the appointed time was long; and he understood the message, and had understanding
        of the vision. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'In those days I, Daniel, was mourning three full weeks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: I ate no pleasant food, no meat or wine came into my mouth, nor did
        I anoint myself at all, till three whole weeks were fulfilled.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now on the twenty-fourth day of the first month, as I was by the
        side of the great river, that is, the Tigris, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I lifted my eyes and looked, and behold, a certain man clothed in
        linen, whose waist was  girded with gold of Uphaz! '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: His body was like beryl, his face like the appearance of lightning,
        his eyes like torches of fire, his arms and feet like burnished bronze in
        color, and the sound of his words like the voice of a multitude.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I, Daniel, alone saw the vision, for the men who were with me
        did not see the vision; but a great terror fell upon them, so that they fled
        to hide themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Therefore I was left alone when I saw this great vision, and no strength
        remained in me; for my vigor was turned to frailty in me, and I retained
        no strength. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Prophecies Concerning Persia and Greece'
      title: Prophecies Concerning Persia and Greece
      number: 9
      content: Yet I heard the sound of his words; and while I heard the sound of
        his words I was in a deep sleep on my face, with my face to the ground.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Suddenly, a hand touched me, which made me tremble on my knees and
        on the palms of my hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And he said to me, \u201CO Daniel, man greatly beloved, understand
        the words that I speak to you, and stand upright, for I have now been sent
        to you.\u201D While he was speaking this word to me, I stood trembling."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then he said to me, \u201CDo not fear, Daniel, for from the first
        day that you set your heart to understand, and to humble yourself before
        your God, your words were heard; and I have come because of your words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But the prince of the kingdom of Persia withstood me twenty-one days;
        and behold, Michael, one of the chief princes, came to help me, for I had
        been left alone there with the kings of Persia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now I have come to make you understand what will happen to your people
        in the latter days, for the vision refers to many days yet to  come.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When he had spoken such words to me, I turned my face toward the
        ground and became speechless. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And suddenly, one having the likeness of the sons of men touched
        my lips; then I opened my mouth and spoke, saying to him who stood before
        me, \u201CMy lord, because of the vision my sorrows have overwhelmed me,
        and I have retained no strength. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For how can this servant of my lord talk with you, my lord? As for
        me, no strength remains in me now, nor is any breath left in me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then again, the  one having the likeness of a man touched me and
        strengthened me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he said, \u201CO man greatly beloved, fear not! Peace be to you;
        be strong, yes, be strong!\u201DSo when he spoke to me I was strengthened,
        and said, \u201CLet my lord speak, for you have strengthened me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then he said, \u201CDo you know why I have come to you? And now I
        must return to fight with the prince of Persia; and when I have gone forth,
        indeed the prince of Greece will come. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: But I will tell you what is noted in the Scripture of Truth. (No one
        upholds me against these, except Michael your prince.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CAlso in the first year of Darius the Mede, I, even I, stood
        up to confirm and strengthen him.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And now I will tell you the truth: Behold, three more kings will
        arise in Persia, and the fourth shall be far richer than them all; by his
        strength, through his riches, he shall stir up all against the realm of Greece. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then a mighty king shall arise, who shall rule with great dominion,
        and do according to his will. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Warring Kings of North and South'
      title: Warring Kings of North and South
      number: 4
      content: And when he has arisen, his kingdom shall be broken up and divided
        toward the four winds of heaven, but not among his posterity nor according
        to his dominion with which he ruled; for his kingdom shall be uprooted, even
        for others besides these.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CAlso the king of the South shall become strong, as well as
        one of his princes; and he shall gain power over him and have dominion. His
        dominion shall  be a great dominion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And at the end of some years they shall join forces, for the daughter
        of the king of the South shall go to the king of the North to make an agreement;
        but she shall not retain the power of her authority, and neither he nor his
        authority shall stand; but she shall be given up, with those who brought
        her, and with him who begot her, and with him who strengthened her in those
        times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But from a branch of her roots one shall arise in his place, who
        shall come with an army, enter the fortress of the king of the North, and
        deal with them and prevail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And he shall also carry their gods captive to Egypt, with their princes
        and their precious articles of silver and gold; and he shall continue more
        years than the king of the North.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAlso the  king  of  the  North shall come to the kingdom of
        the king of the South, but shall return to his own land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: However his sons shall stir up strife, and assemble a multitude of
        great forces; and one shall certainly come and overwhelm and pass through;
        then he shall return to his fortress and stir up strife.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAnd the king of the South shall be moved with rage, and go
        out and fight with him, with the king of the North, who shall muster a great
        multitude; but the multitude shall be given into the hand of his enemy.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When he has taken away the multitude, his heart will be lifted up;
        and he will cast down tens of thousands, but he will not prevail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: For the king of the North will return and muster a multitude greater
        than the former, and shall certainly come at the end of some years with a
        great army and much equipment.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CNow in those times many shall rise up against the king of the
        South. Also, violent men of your people shall exalt themselves in fulfillment
        of the vision, but they shall fall. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So the king of the North shall come and build a siege mound, and
        take a fortified city; and the forces of the South shall not withstand him.
        Even his choice troops shall  have no strength to resist. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: But he who comes against him shall do according to his own will, and
        no one shall stand against him. He shall stand in the Glorious Land with
        destruction in his power.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CHe shall also set his face to enter with the strength of his
        whole kingdom, and upright ones with him; thus shall he do. And he shall
        give him the daughter of women to destroy it; but she shall not stand with 
        him,  or be for him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'After this he shall turn his face to the coastlands, and shall take
        many. But a ruler shall bring the reproach against them to an end; and with
        the reproach removed, he shall turn back on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Then he shall turn his face toward the fortress of his own land; but
        he shall stumble and fall, and not be found.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThere shall arise in his place one who imposes taxes on the
        glorious kingdom; but within a few days he shall be destroyed, but not in
        anger or in battle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And in his place shall arise a vile person, to whom they will not
        give the honor of royalty; but he shall come in peaceably, and seize the
        kingdom by intrigue. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'With the force of a flood they shall be swept away from before him
        and be broken, and also the prince of the covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And after the league is  made with him he shall act deceitfully,
        for he shall come up and become strong with a small number  of people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He shall enter peaceably, even into the richest places of the province;
        and he shall do what his fathers have not done, nor his forefathers: he shall
        disperse among them the plunder, spoil, and riches; and he shall devise his
        plans against the strongholds, but only for a time.'
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CHe shall stir up his power and his courage against the king
        of the South with a great army. And the king of the South shall be stirred
        up to battle with a very great and mighty army; but he shall not stand, for
        they shall devise plans against him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Yes, those who eat of the portion of his delicacies shall destroy
        him; his army shall be swept away, and many shall fall down slain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Both these kings\u2019 hearts shall  be bent on evil, and they shall
        speak lies at the same table; but it shall not prosper, for the end will
        still be at the appointed time. "
      comments: []
    - name: "28: The Northern King\u2019s Blasphemies"
      title: "The Northern King\u2019s Blasphemies"
      number: 28
      content: While returning to his land with great riches, his heart shall be
        moved against the holy covenant; so he shall do damage and return to his
        own land.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CAt the appointed time he shall return and go toward the south;
        but it shall not be like the former or the latter. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "For ships from Cyprus shall come against him; therefore he shall
        be grieved, and return in rage against the holy covenant, and do damage.\u201CSo
        he shall return and show regard for those who forsake the holy covenant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And forces shall be mustered by him, and they shall defile the sanctuary
        fortress; then they shall take away the daily sacrifices, and place there
        the abomination of desolation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Those who do wickedly against the covenant he shall corrupt with
        flattery; but the people who know their God shall be strong, and carry out
        great  exploits.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And those of the people who understand shall instruct many; yet for 
        many days they shall fall by sword and flame, by captivity and plundering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Now when they fall, they shall be aided with a little help; but many
        shall join with them by intrigue. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: And some of those of understanding shall fall, to refine them, purify
        them, and make them white, until the time of the end; because it  is still
        for the appointed time.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CThen the king shall do according to his own will: he shall
        exalt and magnify himself above every god, shall speak blasphemies against
        the God of gods, and shall prosper till the wrath has been accomplished;
        for what has been determined shall be done. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'He shall regard neither the God of his fathers nor the desire of
        women, nor regard any god; for he shall exalt himself above them all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'But in their place he shall honor a god of fortresses; and a god
        which his fathers did not know he shall honor with gold and silver, with
        precious stones and pleasant things. '
      comments: []
    - name: "39: The Northern King\u2019s Conquests"
      title: "The Northern King\u2019s Conquests"
      number: 39
      content: Thus he shall act against the strongest fortresses with a foreign
        god, which he shall acknowledge, and advance its glory; and he shall cause
        them to rule over many, and divide the land for gain.
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CAt the time of the end the king of the South shall attack him;
        and the king of the North shall come against him like a whirlwind, with chariots,
        horsemen, and with many ships; and he shall enter the countries, overwhelm
        them, and pass through. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'He shall also enter the Glorious Land, and many countries shall be
        overthrown; but these shall escape from his hand: Edom, Moab, and the prominent
        people of Ammon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'He shall stretch out his hand against the countries, and the land
        of Egypt shall not escape. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'He shall have power over the treasures of gold and silver, and over
        all the precious things of Egypt; also the Libyans and Ethiopians shall 
        follow  at his heels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'But news from the east and the north shall trouble him; therefore
        he shall go out with great fury to destroy and annihilate many. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: And he shall plant the tents of his palace between the seas and the
        glorious holy mountain; yet he shall come to his end, and no one will help
        him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prophecy of the End Time'
      title: Prophecy of the End Time
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CAt that time Michael shall stand up,The great prince who stands
        watch over the sons of your people;And there shall be a time of trouble,Such
        as never was since there was a nation,Even to that time.And at that time
        your people shall be delivered,Every one who is found written in the book."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And many of those who sleep in the dust of the earth shall awake,Some
        to everlasting life,Some to shame and everlasting contempt.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Those who are wise shall shineLike the brightness of the firmament,And
        those who turn many to righteousnessLike the stars forever and ever.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CBut you, Daniel, shut up the words, and seal the book until
        the time of the end; many shall run to and fro, and knowledge shall increase.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then I, Daniel, looked; and there stood two others, one on this riverbank
        and the other on that riverbank. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And one said to the man clothed in linen, who was above the waters
        of the river, \u201CHow long shall the fulfillment of these wonders be?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Then I heard the man clothed in linen, who was above the waters of
        the river, when he held up his right hand and his left hand to heaven, and
        swore by Him who lives forever, that it  shall  be for a time, times, and
        half a  time;  and when the power of the holy people has been completely
        shattered, all these things shall be finished.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Although I heard, I did not understand. Then I said, \u201CMy lord,
        what shall  be the end of these things?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And he said, \u201CGo your  way, Daniel, for the words are closed
        up and sealed till the time of the end. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Many shall be purified, made white, and refined, but the wicked shall
        do wickedly; and none of the wicked shall understand, but the wise shall
        understand.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAnd from the time that the daily sacrifice is taken away, and
        the abomination of desolation is set up, there  shall  be one thousand two
        hundred and ninety days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Blessed is he who waits, and comes to the one thousand three hundred
        and thirty-five days.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBut you, go your  way till the end; for you shall rest, and
        will arise to your inheritance at the end of the days.\u201D"
      comments: []
